---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import GitHubIcon from "../components/GitHubIcon.astro";
import TerminalWindow from "../components/TerminalWindow.astro";
import MetricStrip from "../components/MetricStrip.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SqueezyAgent - Understand code structure before spending tokens"
  description="SqueezyAgent uses a local static engine to understand code structure before wasting LLM tokens on search."
  active="home"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">local static engine / cost-first coding agent</span>
      <h1>Understand code structure before spending LLM tokens.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        SqueezyAgent is a coding agent built to inspect your repository locally,
        find the right files and symbols, and send the model only the context it
        needs. Less blind search. Less repeated reading. Less wasted spend.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button" href={SITE.repoUrl}><GitHubIcon />Follow on GitHub</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/">Explore the draft docs</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-visual" aria-label="SqueezyAgent terminal preview">
        <TerminalWindow title="squeezy plan --task impact-auth-change">
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <div class="terminal-line">
              <span class="prompt">$</span>
              <span class="command">squeezy ask "what changes if auth middleware moves?"</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-line">
              <span class="green">structure</span>
              <span>auth code connects to routes, sessions, and tests</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-line">
              <span class="cyan">evidence</span>
              <span>6 code slices, 4 callers, 3 tests, reasons attached</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-line">
              <span class="amber">budget</span>
              <span>raw search avoided; compact packet sent to model</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-line">
              <span class="muted">next</span>
              <span>read exact slices only where patching or verification needs code</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </TerminalWindow>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <MetricStrip />

  <section class="section compact">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">current state</span>
      <h2>Runnable foundation today. Code-structure engine next.</h2>
      <p>
        Main already has the TUI foundation, OpenAI Responses streaming,
        Anthropic Messages streaming, deterministic validation harness tasks in
        CI, and bounded fallback tools with receipts and output budgets.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">providers</span>
        <h3>OpenAI and Anthropic streaming.</h3>
        <p>
          Provider tool calls feed structured tool outputs back into the model
          loop instead of bypassing Squeezy's runtime controls.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">tools</span>
        <h3>Bounded fallback navigation exists.</h3>
        <p>
          Ignore-aware grep, path-only glob, capped reads, spill previews,
          aggregate result budgets, and permission-gated web tools are already
          part of the foundation.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">proof</span>
        <h3>Deterministic harness before live spend.</h3>
        <p>
          CI runs mock OpenAI, mock Anthropic, and grep-baseline tasks without
          network access or model cost.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">the problem</span>
      <h2>Agents should not burn tokens just to find the right file.</h2>
      <p>
        Many coding agents still navigate like a model holding search: list
        directories, grep broad text, read whole files, forget after compaction,
        then repeat. That loop is slow and expensive.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">01 / wasted exploration</span>
        <h3>Search noise gets billed like useful reasoning.</h3>
        <p>
          Raw files, noisy shell output, and repeated reads become model context
          even when local analysis could have found the right slice.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">02 / missing structure</span>
        <h3>Text search sees strings, not code relationships.</h3>
        <p>
          Real code work needs files, functions, modules, callers, tests, and
          dependencies. SqueezyAgent is built to find those locally first.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">03 / spend control</span>
        <h3>Teams should own the agent runtime.</h3>
        <p>
          SqueezyAgent is designed to make cost visible and enforceable at the
          navigation layer, not only after the bill arrives.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section band">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">tool-call savings foundation</span>
      <h2>The current runtime already refuses obvious waste.</h2>
      <p>
        Before the code-structure engine lands, SqueezyAgent already makes
        fallback tools cheaper and more accountable. That foundation is what the
        local engine will plug into.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">search</span>
        <h3>Path, count, or content.</h3>
        <p>
          Grep can return matching lines, files with matches, or a count, so
          broad exploration does not always ship raw content to the model.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">spill</span>
        <h3>Large outputs become handles.</h3>
        <p>
          Oversized tool results are stored locally and returned as compact
          previews with exact-range handles.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">budget</span>
        <h3>One round has one budget.</h3>
        <p>
          Parallel tool calls are packed against an aggregate result budget
          instead of each call flooding the next prompt.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">for teams</span>
      <h2>Control agent spend without surrendering the runtime.</h2>
      <p>
        SqueezyAgent is built for organizations and developers who want the
        capability of model-powered agents without letting provider incentives
        define every navigation decision.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">spend visibility</span>
        <h3>Receipts before invoices.</h3>
        <p>
          Track files read, tool output, repeated context avoided, and model
          tokens as first-class runtime facts.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">provider neutral</span>
        <h3>Bring your model. Keep the agent disciplined.</h3>
        <p>
          Routing and budgets belong in the agent runtime, not only in the
          provider billing dashboard.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">local understanding</span>
        <h3>Spend CPU before tokens.</h3>
        <p>
          Build code structure locally, then ask the model to reason over compact
          evidence instead of raw repository noise.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section band">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">the squeezy loop</span>
      <h2>Use local code analysis before paid model context.</h2>
      <p>
        The model should spend tokens on judgment. Your machine should spend CPU
        on finding files, relationships, receipts, and targeted reads before
        billable context enters the prompt.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flow" aria-label="SqueezyAgent semantic navigation flow">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span>input</span>
        <strong>User intent</strong>
        <p>"Move auth middleware without breaking session tests."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span>local</span>
        <strong>Static analysis</strong>
        <p>Parse files, symbols, modules, imports, calls, and tests.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span>graph</span>
        <strong>Structure lookup</strong>
        <p>Find owners, dependencies, callers, tests, and likely impact.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span>packet</span>
        <strong>Evidence packet</strong>
        <p>Return compact code slices, hashes, and reasons.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span>model</span>
        <strong>Targeted context</strong>
        <p>Read slices only when editing or verifying needs text.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">cost control</span>
        <h2>Every read should earn its place in context.</h2>
        <p>
          SqueezyAgent is built around receipts, budgets, deduped reads, compact
          tool output, and local code evidence. The goal is not smaller context for
          its own sake. The goal is better work with less spend.
        </p>
      </div>
      <TerminalWindow title="receipt-backed context packet">
        <div class="terminal-body">
          <div class="terminal-line">
            <span class="cyan">path</span>
            <span>crates/agent/src/session.rs:114..188</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-line">
            <span class="green">reason</span>
            <span>owns compaction receipt replay</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-line">
            <span class="amber">reason</span>
            <span>import path plus local references</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-line">
            <span class="muted">receipt</span>
            <span>sha256:3b2... / unchanged ranges deduped</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </TerminalWindow>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">proof before claims</span>
      <h2>Honest until measured. Sharper when v0 lands.</h2>
      <p>
        This site is a draft surface for a product still being built. Public
        savings claims should come from real receipts, benchmark traces, and
        repeatable correctness checks.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/benchmarks/">Benchmark method</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/">Read the docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
